      <p>Coalition of Relief (COR) is a network of grassroots organisations that work together to provide sustainable long-term support solutions for homelessness.</p>
      <p>By working together they can keep track of and locate people easier, educate and prepare people more effectively, share resources, and save time, money and human lives.<p>

      <h3>Mission and values</h3>
      <p>COR believes in...
        <ul>
          <li><strong>R</strong>esponsible Giving</li>
          <li><strong>E</strong>nlisting your time</li>
          <li><strong>L</strong>ong-Term Support</li>
          <li><strong>I</strong>nspire to empower</li>
          <li><strong>E</strong>Empathy and Respect</li>
          <li><strong>F</strong>unds for proactive change</li>
        </ul>
      </p>

      <h3>Member organisations</h3>
      <p>The current voting members of COR are...
        <ul>
          <li>Community Awareness Network</li>
          <li>Coffee4Craig</li>
          <li>LifeShare</li>
          <li>Breakfast in Bed</li>
          <li>Myriad Foundation</li>
          <li>Sleeping Ruff</li>
          <li>VOW Team</li>
        </ul>
      </p>

      <h3>Joining COR</h3>
      <p>Any Group agreeing with the aims and objectives can apply for full voting membership of COR. Approval is subject to majority vote of the current voting organisations. Please contact <a href="mailto:cor@streetsupport.net">cor@streetsupport.net</a> for more details.</p>


